WEBVTT

00:04.764 --> 00:07.537
[HUEY] <i>Precision. Excellence.
Men in funny hats.</i>

00:07.540 --> 00:09.768
<i>Welcome to the Duckburg
Billionaire's Club</i>

00:09.771 --> 00:10.802
<i>Golf Invitational,</i>

00:10.805 --> 00:12.421
<i>the only golf tournament to take place</i>

00:12.424 --> 00:15.247
<i>on the world's most exotic
and expensive courses.</i>

00:18.658 --> 00:20.403
<i>This year sees Scrooge McDuck</i>

00:20.406 --> 00:22.575
<i>facing off against Flintheart Glomgold,</i>

00:22.578 --> 00:26.767
<i>here at scenic Moorshire,
the birthplace of golf.</i>

00:26.770 --> 00:30.212
I'm Huey Duck, attempting to earn
my Junior Woodchuck Merit Badge

00:30.214 --> 00:31.457
for Sports Commentary.

00:31.460 --> 00:33.430
I'll be here all day
providing nuanced analysis...

00:33.433 --> 00:36.584
Are you ready for some golf?!

00:36.587 --> 00:39.560
[SIGHS] The badge does
require a co-commentator.

00:39.563 --> 00:42.877
Two combatants. One hole. No rules.

00:42.880 --> 00:44.539
That's not actually... Watch out!

00:44.542 --> 00:45.559
Aah!

00:48.110 --> 00:51.186
Get excited, kids. Golf is in our blood!

00:51.189 --> 00:53.806
Your ancestor, "Black Donald" McDuck,

00:53.809 --> 00:55.857
actually invented the sport.

00:55.860 --> 00:57.376
Of course, he lost so badly

00:57.379 --> 00:58.670
that the ensuing temper tantrums

00:58.673 --> 01:01.748
caused King James to ban
golf across all of Scotland.

01:01.751 --> 01:04.313
And we're... proud of that in some way?

01:04.316 --> 01:05.926
I dunno, man. Go-carts?

01:05.929 --> 01:07.503
Hitting things really hard with sticks?

01:07.506 --> 01:09.290
Not being grounded for said hitting?

01:09.293 --> 01:10.654
Sounds kind of awesome.

01:10.657 --> 01:12.531
It's a sport where you
try not to score points

01:12.534 --> 01:14.589
to make it end sooner. Hard pass.

01:14.592 --> 01:16.017
Trust me, you'll love it.

01:16.019 --> 01:18.314
The quiet strategy.

01:18.317 --> 01:20.855
The intense focus.

01:20.857 --> 01:23.174
- The... Aah!
- [HORN BLOWS]

01:23.176 --> 01:26.010
Semi-permanent hearing loss.

01:26.012 --> 01:28.151
Go Scrooge! Boo Glomgold!

01:28.154 --> 01:30.079
Yay custom T-shirts!

01:30.082 --> 01:31.248
- [INHALES]
- [HORN BLOWS]

01:31.251 --> 01:32.855
I'm glad you're excited, dear,

01:32.858 --> 01:35.114
but this sport requires
a certain decorum.

01:35.117 --> 01:37.131
[HUEY] Everybody move!

01:39.902 --> 01:43.822
This lake will be used for the
swimming portion of the competition.

01:47.860 --> 01:50.534
<i>♪ Life is like a hurricane ♪</i>

01:50.537 --> 01:53.142
<i>♪ Here in Duckburg ♪</i>

01:53.145 --> 01:55.959
<i>♪ Race cars, lasers, airplanes ♪</i>

01:55.962 --> 01:58.716
<i>♪ It's a duck-blur ♪</i>

01:58.719 --> 02:01.220
<i>♪ We might solve a mystery ♪</i>

02:01.223 --> 02:03.632
<i>♪ Or rewrite history ♪</i>

02:03.635 --> 02:05.526
<i>♪ Ducktales, whoo-ooh ♪</i>

02:05.529 --> 02:09.878
<i>♪ Every day they're out
there making Ducktales ♪</i>

02:09.882 --> 02:11.298
<i>♪ Whoo-ooh ♪</i>

02:11.301 --> 02:13.314
<i>♪ Tales of derring-do ♪</i>

02:13.317 --> 02:15.226
<i>♪ Bad and good-luck tales ♪</i>

02:15.228 --> 02:16.720
<i>♪ Whoo-ooh ♪</i>

02:16.723 --> 02:19.746
<i>♪ D-d-danger lurks behind you ♪</i>

02:19.749 --> 02:22.111
<i>♪ There's a stranger out to find you ♪</i>

02:22.114 --> 02:23.137
<i>♪ What to do? ♪</i>

02:23.140 --> 02:25.703
<i>♪ Just grab on to some Ducktales ♪</i>

02:25.706 --> 02:27.372
<i>♪ Whoo-ooh ♪</i>

02:27.375 --> 02:29.269
<i>♪ Every day they're out there ♪</i>

02:29.272 --> 02:30.841
<i>♪ Making Ducktales ♪</i>

02:30.844 --> 02:32.417
<i>♪ Whoo-ooh ♪</i>

02:32.420 --> 02:34.744
<i>♪ Tales of daring bad and good ♪</i>

02:34.747 --> 02:37.525
<i>♪ Not phony tales or cottontails ♪</i>

02:37.528 --> 02:39.484
<i>- ♪ No, Ducktales! ♪
- ♪ Whoo-ooh! ♪</i>

02:39.487 --> 02:42.464
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

02:47.629 --> 02:50.447
All right, Webbigail, care
to... What are you doing?

02:50.450 --> 02:53.229
Oh, sorry. I've never
been to a sport before.

02:53.232 --> 02:55.857
But don't worry, I'm
gonna be the best fan!

02:55.860 --> 02:57.268
Did you want to give it a go?

02:57.270 --> 02:59.269
I'm good. Golf clap!

02:59.272 --> 03:01.794
Uh, how about you, lad? Up for a...

03:01.797 --> 03:03.899
Hm? No. Gross. No. Not even a little.

03:03.902 --> 03:05.477
Are you guys kidding me?

03:05.480 --> 03:08.140
A chance to learn the
sport our family invented

03:08.143 --> 03:09.593
from the greatest player who ever lived,

03:09.595 --> 03:10.973
I assume because I don't follow golf?

03:10.975 --> 03:12.979
- I want in.
- Atta boy!

03:12.982 --> 03:16.454
Let's hone that wildly
misplaced enthusiasm, shall we?

03:16.456 --> 03:18.547
We'll start with your swing.

03:18.549 --> 03:20.669
Practice all you want, McDuck!

03:20.672 --> 03:22.809
You won't be winning this year.

03:22.812 --> 03:25.304
You say that every year, Flinty.

03:25.307 --> 03:28.056
And every year you go home crying.

03:28.058 --> 03:29.843
My eyes dry out very easily!

03:29.846 --> 03:34.155
But this year I'll prove that I'm
the best Scottish billionaire golfer!

03:34.158 --> 03:36.322
I've hired the world's best player...

03:36.325 --> 03:38.487
to be my caddie!

03:38.490 --> 03:40.141
Okay, if you want to be a winner,

03:40.144 --> 03:41.711
just follow these three rules...

03:41.714 --> 03:43.313
[GASPS] I'm already a winner!

03:43.316 --> 03:45.240
Nobody tells Flintheart
Glomgold what to do!

03:45.243 --> 03:46.984
You're fired!

03:46.986 --> 03:47.986
Oh!

03:49.989 --> 03:51.413
[STRAINING]

03:51.415 --> 03:52.920
You there! Green one!

03:52.923 --> 03:54.734
How would you like the honor of caddying

03:54.737 --> 03:57.813
under the great Flintheart Glomgold?

03:57.816 --> 03:58.996
Eh.

03:58.998 --> 04:02.166
A chance to bask in the
collective glory of victory?

04:02.168 --> 04:03.517
Blergh.

04:03.519 --> 04:05.336
I tip by the hole.

04:05.338 --> 04:07.242
Ehh, if I'm gonna be bored,

04:07.245 --> 04:08.531
I may as well get paid for it.

04:08.534 --> 04:11.621
Ha! Your own nephew's abandoning you!

04:11.624 --> 04:15.028
Soon, there'll be nobody
left to support you...

04:15.031 --> 04:16.031
- [EXPLOSION]
- [ALL GASP]

04:19.017 --> 04:21.493
Sorry. Timer went off early.

04:21.495 --> 04:23.688
[HORN BLOWING]

04:23.690 --> 04:27.258
Here we are, moments away from
the Classic's opening coin toss.

04:27.261 --> 04:30.426
Glomgold now very obviously
switching the official coin

04:30.429 --> 04:32.463
for one that has "heads" on both sides.

04:32.466 --> 04:34.066
[LAUNCHPAD] Very sneaky.

04:34.069 --> 04:36.073
[HUEY] He tosses the
double-headed coin,

04:36.076 --> 04:38.769
- and Glomgold has called tails.
- What? Aah!

04:38.772 --> 04:42.492
Glomgold, clearly embarrassed, now
trying to throw the coin into the ocean.

04:42.495 --> 04:44.175
- [LAUNCHPAD] He does not make it.
- [SHOUTING ANGRILY]

04:44.177 --> 04:46.543
[HUEY] Scrooge, desperate
to move things along,

04:46.546 --> 04:49.413
has agreed to let Glomgold
"win" the coin toss.

04:49.416 --> 04:50.623
Wow, what a game.

04:50.626 --> 04:52.232
See ya next time, everybody.

04:52.235 --> 04:53.860
It hasn't even... Launchpad!

04:53.863 --> 04:56.680
That coin toss was only
the beginning, Scrooge!

04:56.683 --> 04:59.249
The moment of reckoning
is at hand, and lo...

04:59.252 --> 05:02.560
We've got another ten minutes of
gloating before he takes a shot.

05:02.562 --> 05:04.411
Let's work on your drive.

05:04.413 --> 05:06.289
Hey, get back here!

05:06.292 --> 05:09.519
I'll show you how a real
golfer would play this hole!

05:09.522 --> 05:12.361
All right, boy, how would
your uncle play this hole?

05:12.364 --> 05:13.396
Uh, just...

05:13.399 --> 05:15.433
Why don't ya hit the
ball in the hole, I guess?

05:15.436 --> 05:17.899
Hit the ball... in the hole?

05:17.902 --> 05:18.988
Of course!

05:18.991 --> 05:21.208
I've been over-thinking
it this entire time!

05:26.184 --> 05:28.605
Holy haggis! It stayed on the course!

05:28.608 --> 05:31.204
It went forward. I'm not on fire.

05:31.207 --> 05:34.149
That might be the best
shot I've ever taken!

05:34.152 --> 05:35.659
Nice work, caddie!

05:39.171 --> 05:42.209
Focus. Filter out all distraction.

05:42.212 --> 05:43.552
Go Scrooge!

05:43.555 --> 05:47.848
Now remember: Hips back. Shoulders down.

05:47.851 --> 05:50.839
Tail tucked. Controlled swing.

05:50.842 --> 05:51.842
[GRUNTING]

05:55.615 --> 05:56.797
Was that okay?

05:56.799 --> 05:58.160
Ha ha! You're a natural.

05:58.163 --> 05:59.612
A little unpolished, sure,

05:59.615 --> 06:01.387
but if we can focus that swing,

06:01.390 --> 06:03.006
you'll be almost as good as me one day.

06:03.009 --> 06:03.956
Really?

06:03.959 --> 06:05.107
With a teacher like you,

06:05.110 --> 06:06.459
he could be even better!

06:06.462 --> 06:07.826
Really?!

06:07.829 --> 06:10.112
Or, you know, nearly
as good, but not quite.

06:10.115 --> 06:11.908
After years of hard work and practice.

06:11.911 --> 06:13.124
No need to get the boy's hopes up.

06:13.126 --> 06:15.458
[GLOMGOLD] Scrooge!
Quit stalling! You're up!

06:15.461 --> 06:19.341
Scrooge, the returning champion,
approaching the first hole.

06:19.344 --> 06:20.306
[GOBBLING]

06:20.309 --> 06:23.124
He's probably worried Glomgold
will use his one free tackle

06:23.127 --> 06:25.051
before the speed round
in the third quarter.

06:25.054 --> 06:26.493
What do you think is happening here?

06:26.495 --> 06:28.192
One heck of a game!

06:33.577 --> 06:35.336
Taking his time with the shot...

06:35.338 --> 06:37.544
Tell me about it. Just hit the ball!

06:37.547 --> 06:38.942
Aah! Ohh...

06:40.376 --> 06:42.659
Ouch! And it's deep in the rough.

06:42.662 --> 06:45.451
Ha ha! Nice shot, Scroogey!

06:45.454 --> 06:48.181
Decide to take a shortcut
through the weeds?

06:48.184 --> 06:50.105
Unless... Boy!

06:50.108 --> 06:53.187
Why didn't you tell me about
the shortcut through the weeds?!

06:53.189 --> 06:54.722
Oh, I can't believe it.

06:54.725 --> 06:57.342
I haven't had a shot
that bad in 40 years.

06:59.679 --> 07:01.802
What in the blazes...

07:07.707 --> 07:09.815
[LAUNCHPAD AND HUEY SCREAMING]

07:13.616 --> 07:15.859
[HUEY GROANING]

07:15.862 --> 07:17.856
Ah, yes. Scrooge went for the classic

07:17.859 --> 07:19.773
"magic forest stones" bonus.

07:19.776 --> 07:21.365
Risky, but it paid off.

07:21.368 --> 07:23.480
Oooh, it wasn't a shortcut.

07:23.483 --> 07:27.022
The great McDuck finally
hit a right clunker!

07:27.025 --> 07:28.002
I did not!

07:28.005 --> 07:30.856
I was simply getting
a lay of the terrain.

07:30.859 --> 07:33.058
See, the key to a good golf game...

07:33.061 --> 07:35.652
Take the penalty and let's
get back to the course.

07:35.655 --> 07:39.449
A Scotsman plays it where it lands.

07:40.546 --> 07:42.321
[LOW HUMMING NOISE]

07:46.024 --> 07:47.216
[ELECTRICITY BUZZING]

07:47.219 --> 07:49.310
Um, Mr. McDuck?

07:55.325 --> 07:57.077
Heavenly hollyhock.

07:59.088 --> 08:01.405
[WEBBY] Mythical glowing stones.

08:01.407 --> 08:03.990
Mysterious teleportation circles.

08:03.993 --> 08:06.010
[GASPS] Do you know what this means?

08:06.013 --> 08:08.849
No more golf! Whoo-hoo!

08:08.852 --> 08:11.247
Does anybody see any
clues about where we are?

08:11.250 --> 08:12.674
There are these two orbs.

08:12.676 --> 08:15.243
Hmm, interesting.

08:15.246 --> 08:18.839
And it looks like they'd
fit in that hole over there.

08:18.842 --> 08:20.481
Hm. Okay.

08:21.672 --> 08:24.377
Aah! Cannae touch the blasted things.

08:25.334 --> 08:26.658
- [ZAPPING]
- [GLOMGOLD] Aah!

08:26.661 --> 08:27.752
- [ZAPPING]
- Aah!

08:29.285 --> 08:31.769
Maybe we can use these clubs.

08:31.771 --> 08:34.789
Oh, no. Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

08:40.946 --> 08:43.326
Guys, it's golf. It's still golf!

08:43.328 --> 08:45.179
Okay, that's it, I'm going home.

08:45.182 --> 08:46.450
[RUMBLING]

08:46.452 --> 08:47.968
[GASPS]

08:49.017 --> 08:50.600
Where did home go?

08:52.221 --> 08:54.492
Welcome back to the
Billionaire's Club Classic,

08:54.495 --> 08:56.185
where, in a bizarre turn of events,

08:56.188 --> 08:57.562
the players have become trapped

08:57.565 --> 08:59.797
in some sort of mystical faerie realm.

08:59.799 --> 09:01.833
But they remain undeterred.

09:01.836 --> 09:03.656
For more, we go to two tiny horses.

09:03.659 --> 09:05.041
What are you... Aah!

09:07.075 --> 09:08.339
[HIGH-PITCHED] Greetings!

09:08.342 --> 09:12.008
We're Briar and Bramble,
the keepers of this realm.

09:12.011 --> 09:13.810
Talking animals wearing clothes?!

09:13.813 --> 09:15.662
Oh, no, did we die?

09:15.664 --> 09:17.180
Are we in Webby heaven?

09:17.183 --> 09:19.284
Bet you're all wondering
what this place is.

09:19.287 --> 09:20.977
It's a mystical golf course, right?

09:20.980 --> 09:23.039
Did ancient Scottish
Druids build a secret course

09:23.042 --> 09:24.336
so they could keep playing golf,

09:24.339 --> 09:25.974
even after Black Donald got it banned?

09:25.977 --> 09:28.208
Uh, yep. That's all correct.

09:28.211 --> 09:29.752
Here, hop on our backs!

09:29.755 --> 09:31.759
We'll give you a tour.

09:31.762 --> 09:33.761
Ohh!

09:33.764 --> 09:35.437
Wait. Why are your manes wet?

09:35.440 --> 09:37.952
[GASPS] You're kelpies, aren't you?

09:37.955 --> 09:39.527
You tempt people onto your backs,

09:39.530 --> 09:41.338
then carry them off into the sea!

09:41.340 --> 09:42.998
Oh, no, no, no, no.

09:43.001 --> 09:45.891
We just got out of
the shower, that's all.

09:47.437 --> 09:49.604
Hmm? Hmm!

09:49.606 --> 09:52.349
Fine. That is generally our plan.

09:52.351 --> 09:53.350
Come on, Bramble.

09:53.352 --> 09:55.260
If they're sooo smart,

09:55.263 --> 09:58.621
they must know all about the
treasure at the end of the course.

09:58.624 --> 09:59.623
Treasure?

09:59.698 --> 10:00.646
Treasure?

10:00.649 --> 10:02.028
First to complete this course

10:02.031 --> 10:04.351
will win the priceless Druid's Cup.

10:04.354 --> 10:07.047
Thus proving them to
be the finest golfer

10:07.049 --> 10:09.212
in every plane of reality!

10:09.215 --> 10:10.547
Ooh!

10:10.550 --> 10:11.769
Uh-huh. Okay.

10:11.772 --> 10:13.522
Well anyone else think we should ignore

10:13.525 --> 10:15.358
the murder ponies and go home?

10:15.361 --> 10:17.283
You'll all be sent home safely

10:17.286 --> 10:19.887
as soon as you finish the course.

10:19.890 --> 10:23.304
That is, <i>if</i> you finish the course.

10:23.307 --> 10:29.264
Um. Did we mention the trophy
has custom engraving? Ooh!

10:29.267 --> 10:30.852
Dewey, you've found your calling.

10:32.839 --> 10:36.833
Easy, lad. You can't just flail
that thing at random anymore.

10:36.836 --> 10:38.179
There's too much at stake.

10:38.182 --> 10:40.580
If we lose the ball, we don't go home.

10:40.583 --> 10:43.233
We have got to play smart.

10:43.235 --> 10:45.312
You might want to get started.

10:45.315 --> 10:49.619
It can be awful hard to play
once those mists roll in.

10:53.003 --> 10:54.745
Come on, we're wasting time!

10:54.747 --> 10:56.117
Caddie! My clubs!

10:56.120 --> 10:57.286
Caddie?

10:57.289 --> 10:58.914
Ahem.

11:00.586 --> 11:02.252
Hop on our backs.

11:02.254 --> 11:03.538
We'll take you to the next hole

11:03.541 --> 11:05.665
and definitely not to a watery grave.

11:07.057 --> 11:08.898
You are the least fun victims ever.

11:10.000 --> 11:16.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

11:22.891 --> 11:25.109
What the...?!

11:25.111 --> 11:26.686
Aw, shoulda seen that coming.

11:26.689 --> 11:29.795
How? How could he have
possibly seen that coming?

11:29.798 --> 11:32.658
Give it back, you overgrown puddle!

11:32.661 --> 11:35.482
Aah! Caddie! Help!

11:35.485 --> 11:37.121
Ohh! [STRAINING]

11:37.124 --> 11:38.274
Here!

11:38.277 --> 11:41.918
Oh, it's like you don't
even want to be rescued.

11:48.711 --> 11:50.044
- [ZAPPING]
- [GLOMGOLD] Aah!

11:50.047 --> 11:53.302
Old golf tip: Let
flinty spring that trap,

11:53.305 --> 11:55.400
the rest is just patience.

12:05.113 --> 12:06.253
Patience.

12:08.813 --> 12:09.813
Patience.

12:10.656 --> 12:12.656
Patience!

12:12.658 --> 12:14.500
Uh! If you'd just let me...

12:14.503 --> 12:16.912
Not the time for a reckless clobber.

12:16.915 --> 12:19.897
Come on, ya blasted tentacle!

12:23.086 --> 12:25.078
And besides, you cannae just sub in.

12:25.088 --> 12:26.649
It's against the rules of golf.

12:26.652 --> 12:28.303
[BRIAR] It's okay!

12:28.306 --> 12:31.007
Druid Golf allows for twosomes!

12:31.010 --> 12:33.002
Water's great, by the way!

12:37.183 --> 12:39.070
Oh, give it a go.

12:39.073 --> 12:41.511
But don't get too discouraged
if you don't make it.

12:42.790 --> 12:44.854
Uh-uh-uh-uh-uhh!

12:52.036 --> 12:53.702
Go Dewey!

12:53.705 --> 12:56.265
Good shot, lad. Very proud of you.

12:56.268 --> 12:57.654
You don't sound proud.

12:57.657 --> 12:59.354
Yeah! Scrooge and Dewey,

12:59.357 --> 13:01.871
taking on the world, one hole at time!

13:01.874 --> 13:02.889
[HUEY] There you have it.

13:02.891 --> 13:04.245
Another brash young upstart

13:04.248 --> 13:06.744
destined to surpass his aging mentor.

13:06.747 --> 13:09.070
Is the commentary still necessary?

13:09.073 --> 13:12.905
It helps me feel in control
during a frankly insane situation.

13:12.908 --> 13:14.085
I like talking this way

13:14.088 --> 13:16.385
'cause it makes
everything sound important.

13:16.388 --> 13:19.020
Baloney trampoline.

13:21.060 --> 13:23.076
[MUSIC PLAYING]

14:38.076 --> 14:39.321
[GRUMBLING]

14:49.646 --> 14:50.979
Nailed it!

14:50.982 --> 14:54.391
Whoo-hoo, yeah! Go Dewey!

14:54.394 --> 14:57.119
Scrooge, still in the
lead on the 17th hole,

14:57.122 --> 14:58.745
but Glomgold is closing in.

14:58.748 --> 15:00.465
Hey, so is that weird mist.

15:01.827 --> 15:04.500
Nice job. Nice job.

15:04.503 --> 15:06.497
Aaand nice job.

15:06.500 --> 15:07.437
Not nice enough.

15:07.440 --> 15:08.802
Glomgold's gonna pass us!

15:08.805 --> 15:11.078
You bet your ballast I am!

15:11.081 --> 15:12.514
I'll prove once and for all

15:12.517 --> 15:14.780
I'm the best golfer
in this or any other...

15:14.783 --> 15:17.141
Aah! Caddie!

15:24.999 --> 15:27.349
I'm pretty sure I can get it
to the hole with one swing.

15:27.352 --> 15:28.344
Let me go.

15:28.347 --> 15:30.106
And risk dumping it down into the water?

15:30.109 --> 15:31.521
Absolutely not.

15:31.523 --> 15:33.380
[BRIAR, IMITATING WEBBY]
Aw, give him a chance.

15:33.383 --> 15:35.020
If he hits it in the water,

15:35.023 --> 15:37.193
we can jump on the kelpies to get it!

15:37.196 --> 15:40.460
I'm the small girl
duck. You can trust me.

15:41.700 --> 15:43.375
Oh, whoop!

15:43.378 --> 15:44.508
[SPLASH]

15:44.511 --> 15:46.268
Come on. I can do this!

15:46.271 --> 15:49.054
Do what? Whack the ball blindly?

15:49.057 --> 15:50.553
Into the hole! Yes!

15:50.556 --> 15:51.929
Like I've been doing all day.

15:51.932 --> 15:54.115
Why don't you trust me to make this?

15:54.118 --> 15:55.970
You don't have the experience.

15:55.972 --> 15:57.931
It takes time, effort...

15:57.933 --> 15:58.933
- Hey!
- [GRUNTING]

16:06.685 --> 16:07.884
- Ha ha ha ha ha!
- [CHEERING]

16:07.887 --> 16:08.936
[DEWEY] It's so easy!

16:08.939 --> 16:09.893
No!

16:09.895 --> 16:12.487
[GROWLING]

16:12.489 --> 16:14.204
I'm sorry. I just knew I could, so I...

16:14.207 --> 16:16.159
You pull a club out
of a Scotsman's hand,

16:16.162 --> 16:18.505
you'd best be prepared
to knock him out with it!

16:18.508 --> 16:20.229
Hey, I made the shot.

16:20.232 --> 16:21.856
You disobeyed me

16:21.859 --> 16:24.499
and risked the entire
game with your showboating!

16:24.502 --> 16:26.093
I'm showboating?

16:26.096 --> 16:28.149
This whole thing has been
about how great you are.

16:28.152 --> 16:30.449
You're so worried that someone
might actually be better than you

16:30.451 --> 16:31.248
at something that you keep...

16:31.250 --> 16:35.506
See here, I am an
inter-dimensionally ranked golfer!

16:35.509 --> 16:37.636
Whatever. I'm over
this dumb sport anyway.

16:37.639 --> 16:39.405
Finish the course so we can go home.

16:41.109 --> 16:43.931
Now hold on. I didn't mean to...

16:46.966 --> 16:48.946
- [WHACK]
- [GLOMGOLD] Outta the way, McDuck!

16:49.859 --> 16:50.876
Hah!

17:00.779 --> 17:03.290
[HUEY] The last hole.

17:03.293 --> 17:05.798
Looks like some sort of Hall of Fame.

17:05.800 --> 17:10.226
Well, your old Uncle Scrooge will
be joining it soon enough, eh?

17:10.229 --> 17:11.493
Let's get this over with.

17:15.965 --> 17:18.531
Scrooge, lining up, and none too soon.

17:18.535 --> 17:20.395
Morale is not high.

17:20.397 --> 17:22.124
Uh, Mr. McDuck?

17:22.127 --> 17:24.633
Those mists are getting really close.

17:24.636 --> 17:26.980
Well, that's ominous.

17:30.993 --> 17:33.152
[HUEY] And he hooks it onto the wall.

17:39.841 --> 17:41.835
Nice work. How are you
going to get up there?

17:41.837 --> 17:42.910
[GLOMGOLD] It's happening.

17:42.912 --> 17:44.105
I'm one stroke away

17:44.108 --> 17:47.107
from claiming the trophy
and beating Scrooge McDuck!

17:47.110 --> 17:50.802
As soon as I take this
swing, I, Flintheart Glomgold,

17:50.805 --> 17:53.630
will be the winner of the
Billionaire's Club Classic.

17:53.633 --> 17:56.349
Sure, you may have won the previous 27,

17:56.352 --> 17:58.053
but I think we can all agree

17:58.056 --> 18:00.114
this one counts more
than the rest combined.

18:00.117 --> 18:01.554
Uh, Flinty?

18:01.557 --> 18:02.674
Stuff it, Scrooge.

18:02.677 --> 18:03.839
I'm savoring the moment.

18:03.842 --> 18:05.298
Caddie, savor with me.

18:05.301 --> 18:06.510
Caddie?

18:06.512 --> 18:07.512
[GROWLS]

18:08.951 --> 18:10.283
Um...

18:10.286 --> 18:12.195
Oh. I see.

18:12.198 --> 18:13.467
Curse you, McDuck!

18:13.470 --> 18:15.701
Curse you and my love
of moment-savoring!

18:15.704 --> 18:17.223
Aah!

18:18.543 --> 18:21.257
The mist turns people to stone!

18:21.260 --> 18:23.011
Those statues used to be real golfers!

18:23.014 --> 18:24.104
[SINISTER LAUGHTER]

18:24.107 --> 18:26.350
Oh, by the way, the mists of Moorshire?

18:26.353 --> 18:28.019
They turn mortals to stone.

18:28.022 --> 18:29.127
Those statues are...

18:29.130 --> 18:31.694
You just said all that, didn't you?

18:33.205 --> 18:34.572
So you're doomed.

18:34.575 --> 18:36.774
Better to let us drown
you instead. Let's go!

18:36.777 --> 18:38.224
[ALL] No!

18:38.226 --> 18:40.250
You people are no fun.

18:47.736 --> 18:49.462
We have to finish the course.

18:49.465 --> 18:52.145
Those hoofed hostiles
said it would get us home.

18:52.148 --> 18:53.603
[GRUNTING]

18:56.596 --> 18:59.269
Everybody! We need to support Scrooge!

18:59.272 --> 19:02.086
Why? He hasn't supported me all day.

19:02.089 --> 19:04.851
No, we need to <i>support</i> Scrooge.

19:04.854 --> 19:06.329
Not everything is a life lesson!

19:13.095 --> 19:15.345
[ALL STRAINING]

19:20.009 --> 19:21.498
Louie! Hand me the club!

19:23.355 --> 19:25.456
Oh, right, sure. Nope, not the time.

19:27.353 --> 19:29.000
Oh, my.

19:29.003 --> 19:31.738
Scrooge, taking his
time, I'm not sure why.

19:31.741 --> 19:33.175
There are lives at stake.

19:33.178 --> 19:35.098
Wait, whose?

19:35.100 --> 19:37.100
Oh, right.

19:37.102 --> 19:38.503
[GROANS]

19:38.506 --> 19:40.269
This has been Huey Duck, signing off!

19:40.272 --> 19:41.873
Man, I hate this sport.

19:41.876 --> 19:44.675
[WEBBY] Come on, Scrooge,
I know you can do it.

19:44.678 --> 19:46.423
Webby! Guys! No!

19:46.426 --> 19:47.627
What are you waiting for?

19:47.629 --> 19:49.871
Take the stupid shot!

19:49.873 --> 19:51.278
- Not me.
- What?

19:51.281 --> 19:53.195
I cannae make the shot. You can.

19:57.549 --> 19:59.824
I know you can do it.

20:01.880 --> 20:04.047
Okay, okay. Filter out all distractions.

20:04.050 --> 20:06.233
Hips back. Shoulders down. Tail tucked.

20:06.236 --> 20:08.026
Aah! Whack the ball! Whack the ball!

20:17.792 --> 20:19.233
[BELL RINGS]

20:19.236 --> 20:20.236
Yes!

20:26.151 --> 20:27.584
- Aah!
- Oof!

20:30.619 --> 20:33.914
You did it, lad! I knew you could!

20:33.917 --> 20:36.326
[BRIAR] Congratulations, champions!

20:36.328 --> 20:38.362
You are the first players

20:38.365 --> 20:40.406
to ever complete the Druid's Cup.

20:41.833 --> 20:43.921
Go on. You earned it.

20:47.673 --> 20:50.007
[DEWEY] "Scroge" and "Douise"?

20:50.010 --> 20:51.768
Sorry. It was a rush job.

20:51.771 --> 20:53.905
We really didn't expect you to make it.

20:53.908 --> 20:57.179
Now, who's up for a victory swim?

20:57.182 --> 20:58.531
[ALL] No!

20:59.422 --> 21:00.422
Yaah!

21:04.876 --> 21:07.862
You! You let me turn to stone!

21:07.865 --> 21:11.106
You're the worst caddie
ever! You're fired!

21:12.280 --> 21:15.031
As soon as you help me out.

21:15.033 --> 21:16.475
Ahh!

21:20.787 --> 21:22.871
- [WHACK]
- [GLOMGOLD SCREAMS]

21:22.874 --> 21:24.465
You know, we could use another player

21:24.467 --> 21:26.138
for next year's Invitational.

21:26.141 --> 21:28.877
I'd love someone who actually
gave me a run for my money.

21:28.880 --> 21:30.897
Eh, I think my pro career is over.

21:30.899 --> 21:32.082
I'm going out on top.

21:32.085 --> 21:34.474
Still, I'd be up for a
friendly round now and then.

21:34.477 --> 21:36.310
Sounds grand.

21:36.312 --> 21:37.977
Whooo! Screwy for life!

21:37.980 --> 21:39.888
In your face, everybody who's not them!

21:39.891 --> 21:40.987
Whoo-hoo!

21:40.990 --> 21:43.409
Maybe just the two of us.

21:43.411 --> 21:45.005
Well, there you have it, folks.

21:45.008 --> 21:46.602
Scrooge let go of his ego

21:46.605 --> 21:48.710
and learned that a good teacher's pride

21:48.713 --> 21:51.302
should be in his student, not himself.

21:51.305 --> 21:54.123
That's... actually a good insight.

21:54.126 --> 21:56.305
Wow, I'm impressed, Launchpad.

21:56.308 --> 21:58.258
And you're choking on golf balls.

21:58.261 --> 22:00.279
They look like tasty eggs!

22:00.282 --> 22:02.784
I resisted for so long!

